Rachel,

Good afternoon. I'm submitting for quote on behalf of Westfield Retail
Properties LLC ahead of their May 1, 2024 expiration. This is a new account
for Pinnacle — they were previously with Hartfield Mutual, who non-renewed
them following a commercial lines underwriting review (not a loss-driven
non-renewal; Hartfield exited the retail segment in IL and WI).

Account Overview:
  Insured:         Westfield Retail Properties LLC
  FEIN:            82-4471938
  Mailing Address: 3300 Commerce Park Drive, Downers Grove, IL 60515
  Operations:      Owner/operator of strip mall and neighborhood retail centers
  Years in Business: 17 years

Schedule Summary:
  - 8 locations across Illinois, Wisconsin, and Indiana
  - Total square footage: approximately 310,000 sq ft
  - TIV: $28.6M (Building) + $4.1M (Business Personal Property)
  - Largest location: Brookfield, WI (~72,000 sq ft, $6.8M building value)
  - All locations are occupied; typical tenants include grocery anchors,
    national drug chains, and local service retailers

Coverage Requested:
  - Commercial Property: Special Form, RC, blanket limit $35M
  - General Liability: $1M/$2M (submit separately — GL package coming Thursday)
  - Business Income: Actual Loss Sustained, 18-month extended period
  - Deductible: $50,000 AOP; $100,000 Named Storm

Loss History (5 years):
  - 2023: No losses
  - 2022: $18,400 water damage claim (Kenosha, WI) — subrogation recovered $11,200
  - 2021: No losses
  - 2020: $7,800 slip-and-fall (GL, not property) — closed
  - 2019: No losses

Please quote on a monoline property basis. Client is also open to package
if Pinnacle can be competitive on GL. Target premium is $185,000 for the
property line.

Please confirm receipt and advise your turnaround timeline.

